He learned things, and he will testify in exchange for early parole.

280
00:24:06,880 --> 00:24:08,980
Rachel, this man killed my parents.

281
00:24:11,180 --> 00:24:15,460
I cannot let that pass, and I need you to understand that, please.

282
00:24:17,900 --> 00:24:18,240
Okay.

283
00:24:20,160 --> 00:24:23,080
The Depression hit working people like Mr. Chill hardest of all.

284
00:24:23,200 --> 00:24:27,960
His crime was appalling, yes, but it was motivated not by greed, but by desperation.

285
00:24:29,140 --> 00:24:34,960
And given the 14 years already served, as well as his extraordinary level of cooperation with one of this office's most important investigations,

286
00:24:35,840 --> 00:24:37,820
we strongly endorse his petition for early release.

287
00:24:40,180 --> 00:24:40,900
Mr. Chill?

288
00:24:45,840 --> 00:24:51,080
Your Honor, not a day goes by that I don't wish I could take back what I did.

289
00:24:53,280 --> 00:24:56,540
Sure, I was desperate, like a lot of people back then,

290
00:24:57,660 --> 00:24:58,540
but that don't change what I did.

291
00:25:03,580 --> 00:25:07,860
I gather there's a member of the Wayne family here today.

292
00:25:08,560 --> 00:25:09,720
Has he got anything to say?

293
00:25:23,200 --> 00:25:26,360
Coming out the side.

294
00:25:27,080 --> 00:25:28,120
Coming out the side, guys.

295
00:25:37,280 --> 00:25:41,920
Hey, Joe.

296
00:25:43,780 --> 00:25:44,700
Don't call this his car.

297
00:25:53,200 --> 00:25:55,740
Oh, Bruce.

298
00:25:56,800 --> 00:25:57,820
We don't need to see this.

299
00:25:59,760 --> 00:26:00,140
I do.

300
00:26:06,440 --> 00:26:08,280
The D.A. couldn't understand why Judge Faden

301
00:26:08,280 --> 00:26:10,120
insisted on making the hearing public.

302
00:26:10,740 --> 00:26:12,760
Falcone paid him off to get Chill out in the open.

303
00:26:13,120 --> 00:26:14,280
Maybe I should be thanking them.

304
00:26:14,680 --> 00:26:15,300
You don't mean that.

305
00:26:15,620 --> 00:26:16,560
What if I do, Rachel?

306
00:26:17,380 --> 00:26:18,700
My parents deserve justice.

307
00:26:19,380 --> 00:26:20,700
You're not talking about justice.

308
00:26:21,020 --> 00:26:22,060
You're talking about revenge.

309
00:26:22,300 --> 00:26:23,400
Sometimes they're the same.

310
00:26:23,680 --> 00:26:25,020
No, they're never the same, Bruce.

311
00:26:25,480 --> 00:26:26,560
Justice is about harmony.

312
00:26:26,620 --> 00:26:28,940
Revenge is about you making yourself feel better.

313
00:26:29,400 --> 00:26:30,840
That is why we have an impartial system.

314
00:26:31,100 --> 00:26:32,260
Well, your system is broken.

315
00:26:39,840 --> 00:26:40,840
You care about justice?

316
00:26:41,340 --> 00:26:42,720
Look beyond your own pain, Bruce.

317
00:26:42,740 --> 00:26:44,180
This city is rotting.

318
00:26:44,680 --> 00:26:47,220
They talk about the Depression as if it's history, and it's not.

319
00:26:47,520 --> 00:26:48,940
Things are worse than ever down here.

320
00:26:49,040 --> 00:26:54,660
Falcone floods our streets with crime and drugs, preying on the desperate, creating new Joe Chills every day.

321
00:26:55,140 --> 00:26:57,180
You know, Falcone may not have killed your parents, Bruce.

322
00:26:58,280 --> 00:27:00,240
But he's destroying everything that they stood for.

323
00:27:04,940 --> 00:27:06,660
You want to thank him for that? Here you go.

324
00:27:10,140 --> 00:27:11,140
We all know where to find him.

325
00:27:11,560 --> 00:27:14,770
But as long as he keeps the bad people rich and the good people scared, no one will touch him.

326
00:27:14,770 --> 00:27:18,820
If good people like your parents will stand against injustice, they're gone.

327
00:27:19,040 --> 00:27:22,440
What chance does Gotham have when the good people do nothing?

328
00:27:24,540 --> 00:27:26,120
I'm not one of your good people, Rachel.

329
00:27:26,860 --> 00:27:27,500
What do you mean?

330
00:27:30,340 --> 00:27:32,040
All these years I wanted to kill him.

331
00:27:34,000 --> 00:27:34,820
Now I can't.

332
00:27:49,140 --> 00:27:50,640
Your father would be ashamed of you.

333
00:28:19,040 --> 00:28:39,000
You're taller than you look in the tabloids, Mr. Wayne.

334
00:28:39,640 --> 00:28:40,900
No gun. I'm insulted.

335
00:28:44,100 --> 00:28:46,110
You could have just sent a thank you note.

336
00:28:46,110 --> 00:28:47,520
I didn't come here to thank you.

337
00:28:48,740 --> 00:28:51,400
I came here to show you that not everyone at Gotham's afraid of you.

338
00:28:51,620 --> 00:28:52,820
Only those who know me, kid.

339
00:28:53,560 --> 00:28:54,220
Look around you.

340
00:28:54,780 --> 00:29:00,180
You'll see two consulmen, a union official, a couple off-duty cops, and a judge.

341
00:29:00,940 --> 00:29:05,620
Now, I wouldn't have a second's hesitation in blowing your head off right here and right now in front of them.

342
00:29:05,780 --> 00:29:07,200
Now, that's power you can't buy.

343
00:29:09,280 --> 00:29:10,380
That's the power of fear.

344
00:29:11,220 --> 00:29:12,080
I'm not afraid of you.

345
00:29:12,540 --> 00:29:14,200
Because you think you've got nothing to lose.

346
00:29:14,280 --> 00:29:15,500
But you haven't thought it through.

347
00:29:15,600 --> 00:29:19,160
You haven't thought about your lady friend down in the DA's office.

348
00:29:19,660 --> 00:29:21,300
You haven't thought about your old butler.

349
00:29:21,880 --> 00:29:22,060
Bang!

350
00:29:26,320 --> 00:29:30,220
People from your world have so much to lose.

351
00:29:31,420 --> 00:29:35,260
Now you think because your mommy and your daddy got shot,

352
00:29:35,840 --> 00:29:38,500
you know about the ugly side of life, but you don't.

353
00:29:38,920 --> 00:29:40,360
You've never tasted desperate.

354
00:29:41,240 --> 00:29:43,940
You're Bruce Wayne, the Prince of Gotham.

355
00:29:44,020 --> 00:29:46,640
you'd have to go a thousand miles to meet someone who didn't know your name.

356
00:29:46,780 --> 00:29:49,260
So don't come down here with your anger,

357
00:29:49,760 --> 00:29:51,480
trying to prove something to yourself.

358
00:29:52,080 --> 00:29:53,400
This is a world you'll never understand,

359
00:29:54,140 --> 00:29:57,360
and you always fear what you don't understand.

360
00:30:01,720 --> 00:30:02,080
All right.

361
00:30:10,160 --> 00:30:12,820
Yeah, you got spirit, kid. I'll give you that.

362
00:30:14,020 --> 00:30:15,160
More than your old man, anyway.

363
00:30:16,000 --> 00:30:17,420
In the joint, Chill told me, uh,

364
00:30:18,020 --> 00:30:19,780
told me about the night he killed your parents.

365
00:30:20,580 --> 00:30:22,140
They said your father begged for mercy.

366
00:30:24,080 --> 00:30:24,340
Begged.

367
00:30:25,980 --> 00:30:26,540
Like a dog.

368
00:30:39,940 --> 00:30:41,320
Should've did better.

369
00:30:44,620 --> 00:30:45,440
I'm gonna go.

370
00:30:51,520 --> 00:30:52,340
What?

371
00:30:52,640 --> 00:30:53,420
Your jacket.

372
00:30:54,460 --> 00:30:54,700
Okay.

373
00:30:57,120 --> 00:31:00,200
Hey, hey, hey. Let me have some nice clothes.

374
00:31:00,480 --> 00:31:01,940
Be careful he sees you with that.

375
00:31:03,340 --> 00:31:04,360
They're gonna come looking for me.

376
00:31:04,560 --> 00:31:04,800
Who?

377
00:31:05,760 --> 00:31:06,000
Everyone.

378
00:31:11,500 --> 00:31:12,940
Some nice clothes.

379
00:31:32,100 --> 00:31:35,400
When you lived among the criminals, did you start to pity them?

380
00:31:36,380 --> 00:31:39,480
The first time I stole so that I wouldn't starve, yes.

381
00:31:39,660 --> 00:31:45,060
I lost many assumptions about the simple nature of right and wrong.

382
00:31:47,240 --> 00:31:54,820
And when I traveled, I learned the fear before a crime and the thrill of success.

383
00:31:57,280 --> 00:31:58,940
But I never became one of them.

384
00:32:02,100 --> 00:32:05,220
Fool, what the hell do I care what your name is? You're a criminal.

385
00:32:06,520 --> 00:32:08,060
Tell that to the guy who owned these.

386
00:32:09,660 --> 00:32:15,720
You've traveled the world to understand the criminal mind and conquer your fears.

387
00:32:18,000 --> 00:32:20,680
But the criminal is not complicated.

388
00:32:22,420 --> 00:32:24,400
What you really fear is inside yourself.

389
00:32:25,800 --> 00:32:27,660
You fear your own power.

390
00:32:28,680 --> 00:32:34,100
You fear your anger, the drive to do great or terrible things.

391
00:32:35,060 --> 00:32:37,080
Now you must journey inwards.

392
00:32:42,060 --> 00:32:42,660
You are ready.

393
00:32:45,140 --> 00:32:45,460
Breathe.

394
00:32:55,560 --> 00:32:56,500
Breathe.

395
00:33:03,080 --> 00:33:04,000
Breathe in your fears.

396
00:33:07,240 --> 00:33:08,080
Face them.

397
00:33:09,560 --> 00:33:11,880
To conquer fear, you must become fear.

398
00:33:12,960 --> 00:33:14,740
You must bask in the fear of other men.

399
00:33:17,640 --> 00:33:19,860
And men fear most what they cannot see.

400
00:33:38,400 --> 00:33:40,140
You have to become a terrible thought.

401
00:33:45,040 --> 00:33:46,620
A wraith.

402
00:33:51,980 --> 00:33:53,680
You have to become an idea!

403
00:33:58,060 --> 00:34:04,320
Feel Terra cloud your senses.

404
00:34:06,680 --> 00:34:08,500
Feel its power to distort.

405
00:34:10,900 --> 00:34:11,360
To control.

406
00:34:16,300 --> 00:34:18,800
And know that this power can be yours.

407
00:34:28,060 --> 00:34:33,960
Embrace your worst fear.

408
00:34:41,600 --> 00:34:43,679
Become one with the darkness.

409
00:35:04,460 --> 00:35:04,480
Focus.

410
00:35:06,260 --> 00:35:07,140
Concentrate.

411
00:35:08,600 --> 00:35:09,880
Master your senses.

412
00:35:38,980 --> 00:35:40,600
You cannot leave any sign.

413
00:35:41,820 --> 00:35:42,300
I haven't.

414
00:35:50,880 --> 00:35:51,960
Impressive.

415
00:35:54,540 --> 00:35:55,620
Agatero Taveroso.

416
00:35:58,060 --> 00:36:03,980
We have purged your fear.

417
00:36:05,440 --> 00:36:06,820
You are ready to lead these men.

418
00:36:07,480 --> 00:36:09,560
You are ready to become a member of the League of Shadows.

419
00:36:13,300 --> 00:36:16,640
But first, you must demonstrate your commitment to justice.

420
00:36:17,740 --> 00:36:17,960
I will.

421
00:36:28,060 --> 00:36:38,460
I'm no executioner.

422
00:36:39,240 --> 00:36:42,240
Your compassion is a weakness your enemies will not share.

423
00:36:43,140 --> 00:36:44,280
That's why it's so important.

424
00:36:45,760 --> 00:36:47,190
It separates us from them.

425
00:36:47,190 --> 00:36:49,740
You want to fight criminals. This man is a murderer.

426
00:36:50,000 --> 00:36:50,880
This man should be tried.

427
00:36:51,420 --> 00:36:53,120
By whom? Corrupt bureaucrats?

428
00:36:54,100 --> 00:36:55,900
Criminals mock society's laws.

429
00:36:56,140 --> 00:36:57,960
You know those better than most.

430
00:36:59,960 --> 00:37:06,240
You cannot lead these men unless you are prepared to do what is necessary to defeat evil.

431
00:37:07,320 --> 00:37:09,040
Where would I be leading these men?

432
00:37:10,120 --> 00:37:13,240
Gotham. As Gotham's favored son.

433
00:37:13,760 --> 00:37:17,420
You will be ideally placed to strike at the heart of criminality.

434
00:37:18,600 --> 00:37:18,720
How?

435
00:37:18,720 --> 00:37:21,280
Gotham's time has come.

436
00:37:22,460 --> 00:37:25,060
Like Constantinople or Rome before it.

437
00:37:25,140 --> 00:37:29,200
The city has become a breeding ground for suffering and injustice.

438
00:37:30,460 --> 00:37:33,120
It is beyond saving and must be allowed to die.

439
00:37:34,240 --> 00:37:38,760
This is the most important function of the League of Shadows.

440
00:37:39,700 --> 00:37:41,460
It is one we performed for centuries.

441
00:37:43,340 --> 00:37:46,200
Gotham must be destroyed.

442
00:37:50,980 --> 00:37:52,760
You can't believe in us.

443
00:37:52,880 --> 00:37:56,740
Ra's al Ghul rescued us from the darkest corners of our own hearts.

444
00:37:57,640 --> 00:38:01,640
What he asks in return is the courage to do what is necessary.

445
00:38:02,320 --> 00:38:08,020
I will go back to Gotham and I will fight men like this, but I will not become an executioner.

446
00:38:08,420 --> 00:38:12,500
Bruce, please. For your own sake, there is no turning back.

447
00:38:45,440 --> 00:38:45,690
What are you doing?

448
00:38:45,690 --> 00:38:47,020
It was necessary, my friend.

449
00:39:49,720 --> 00:39:52,300
I'm sorry.

450
00:40:48,740 --> 00:40:52,860
Oh, my God.

451
00:40:52,880 --> 00:41:06,960
I will tell him you said he's alive.

452
00:41:22,880 --> 00:41:28,640
Master Wayne, you've been gone a long time.

453
00:41:29,020 --> 00:41:29,560
Yes, I have.

454
00:41:29,880 --> 00:41:30,760
You look very fashionable.

455
00:41:32,680 --> 00:41:33,440
Apart from the mud.

456
00:41:34,480 --> 00:41:36,240
Were you coming back to Gotham for long, sir?

457
00:41:37,180 --> 00:41:38,080
As long as it takes.

458
00:41:38,740 --> 00:41:40,040
I'm going to show the people of Gotham

459
00:41:40,040 --> 00:41:42,660
their city doesn't belong to the criminals and the corrupt.

460
00:41:44,120 --> 00:41:44,490
In the Depression,

461
00:41:44,490 --> 00:41:47,280
your father nearly bankrupted Wayne Enterprises

462
00:41:47,280 --> 00:41:48,420
combating poverty.

463
00:41:48,860 --> 00:41:50,900
He believed that his example could inspire

464
00:41:51,140 --> 00:41:53,280
the wealthy of Gotham to save their city.

465
00:41:53,780 --> 00:41:54,000
Did it?

466
00:41:56,440 --> 00:41:56,640
Anyway,

467
00:41:57,760 --> 00:41:59,100
their murder shot the wealthy

468
00:41:59,100 --> 00:42:00,600
and the powerful into action.

469
00:42:03,120 --> 00:42:04,900
People need dramatic examples

470
00:42:04,900 --> 00:42:06,240
to shake them out of apathy,

471
00:42:06,240 --> 00:42:07,720
and I can't do that as Bruce Wayne.

472
00:42:08,240 --> 00:42:10,640
As a man, I'm flesh and blood.

473
00:42:10,860 --> 00:42:12,240
I can be ignored, I can be destroyed,

474
00:42:12,400 --> 00:42:13,200
but as a symbol...

475
00:42:15,640 --> 00:42:17,780
as a symbol, I can be incorruptible.

476
00:42:18,560 --> 00:42:19,500
I can be everlasting.

477
00:42:20,460 --> 00:42:20,880
What symbol?

478
00:42:21,140 --> 00:42:22,440
Something...

479
00:42:23,480 --> 00:42:25,560
elemental, something terrifying.

480
00:42:26,500 --> 00:42:28,620
I assume that as you're taking on the Underworld,

481
00:42:28,640 --> 00:42:33,420
this symbol is a persona to protect those you care about from reprisals.

482
00:42:34,120 --> 00:42:34,940
You thinking about Rachel?

483
00:42:35,580 --> 00:42:37,360
Rachel, you tell. I was thinking of myself.

484
00:42:40,100 --> 00:42:41,440
Have you told anyone I'm coming back?

485
00:42:42,020 --> 00:42:42,900
I just couldn't figure.

486
00:42:43,420 --> 00:42:46,000
The legal ramifications of bringing you back from the dead.

487
00:42:46,340 --> 00:42:46,600
Dead?

488
00:42:47,180 --> 00:42:48,240
You've been gone seven years.

489
00:42:48,380 --> 00:42:49,250
You have me declared dead?

490
00:42:49,250 --> 00:42:52,400
Well, actually, it was Mr. Earl. He's taking the company public.

491
00:42:52,940 --> 00:42:54,620
He wanted to liquidate your majority shareholding.

492
00:42:55,220 --> 00:42:56,520
Those shares are worth quite a bit of money.

493
00:42:57,860 --> 00:43:00,100
Well, it's a good thing I left everything to you, then.

494
00:43:01,040 --> 00:43:01,840
Quite so, sir.

495
00:43:03,080 --> 00:43:04,440
And you can borrow the rolls if you like.

496
00:43:04,780 --> 00:43:06,060
Just bring it back with a full tank.

497
00:43:16,780 --> 00:43:21,200
In my opinion, Mr. Zaz is as much a danger to himself as to others.

498
00:43:21,840 --> 00:43:24,980
And prison is probably not the best environment for his rehabilitation.

499
00:43:28,360 --> 00:43:29,220
Dr. Crane?

500
00:43:30,180 --> 00:43:30,900
Ah, Mr. Oz.

501
00:43:31,480 --> 00:43:34,480
You really think a man who butchers people for the mob doesn't belong in jail?

502
00:43:34,560 --> 00:43:37,340
I only would hardly have testified to that otherwise, would I, Miss Dawes?

503
00:43:37,740 --> 00:43:42,180
This is the third of Carmine Falcone's thugs you've had declared insane and moved into your asylum.

504
00:43:42,660 --> 00:43:45,960
Well, the work offered by organized crime must have an attraction to the insane.

505
00:43:48,780 --> 00:43:49,540
Or the corrupt.

506
00:43:53,000 --> 00:43:56,770
Mr. Finch, I think you should check with Miss Dawes here

507
00:43:56,770 --> 00:43:59,360
just what implications your office has authorized her to make.

508
00:44:00,280 --> 00:44:00,580
If any.

509
00:44:04,940 --> 00:44:05,960
What are you doing, Rachel?

510
00:44:06,080 --> 00:44:07,060
What are you doing, Carl?

511
00:44:07,740 --> 00:44:08,620
Looking out for you.

512
00:44:11,640 --> 00:44:13,080
Falcone has half the city.

513
00:44:13,500 --> 00:44:14,300
Bought and paid for.

514
00:44:14,820 --> 00:44:15,290
Drop it.

515
00:44:15,290 --> 00:44:16,580
How can you say that?

516
00:44:17,000 --> 00:44:18,620
Because as much as I care about getting Falcone,

517
00:44:18,660 --> 00:44:19,840
I care more about you.

518
00:44:20,680 --> 00:44:21,140
That's sweet.

519
00:44:27,540 --> 00:44:28,380
We've been through all that.

520
00:44:56,160 --> 00:44:57,080
Bless it, Badagetsu.

521
00:44:58,000 --> 00:44:59,120
It nests somewhere in the grounds.

522
00:45:57,980 --> 00:45:58,040
I don't know.

523
00:46:25,460 --> 00:46:25,500
Thank you.

524
00:46:57,980 --> 00:46:58,020
Thank you.

525
00:46:58,020 --> 00:47:00,640
No more favors. Someone is sniffing around.

526
00:47:01,160 --> 00:47:03,980
Hey, I scratch your back, you scratch mine, Doc.

527
00:47:03,980 --> 00:47:05,460
I'm bringing in the shipments.

528
00:47:06,240 --> 00:47:07,220
We are paying you for that.

529
00:47:07,740 --> 00:47:09,960
Maybe money isn't as interesting to me as favors.

530
00:47:12,580 --> 00:47:16,920
I am more than aware that you are not intimidated by me, Mr. Falcone.

531
00:47:17,520 --> 00:47:19,280
But you know who I'm working for.

532
00:47:19,280 --> 00:47:20,940
And when he gets here...

533
00:47:21,640 --> 00:47:22,560
He's coming to Gotham?

534
00:47:23,080 --> 00:47:23,560
Yes, he is.

535
00:47:23,700 --> 00:47:28,420
And when he gets here, he's not going to want to hear that you have endangered our operation

536
00:47:28,700 --> 00:47:30,920
just to get your thugs out of a little jail time.

537
00:47:33,240 --> 00:47:34,140
Who's bothering you?

538
00:47:34,560 --> 00:47:36,140
There's a girl at the DA's office.

539
00:47:37,200 --> 00:47:37,940
Well, buy her off.

540
00:47:38,180 --> 00:47:38,760
Not this one.

541
00:47:40,220 --> 00:47:40,940
Idealist, huh?

542
00:47:42,080 --> 00:47:43,580
Well, there's an answer to that, too.

543
