This is where we make the medicine.

1086
01:26:06,400 --> 01:26:07,600
Perhaps you should have something

1087
01:26:08,880 --> 01:26:09,880
to clear your head.

1088
01:26:35,520 --> 01:26:36,260
I'm not your hater.

1089
01:26:46,120 --> 01:26:47,320
He's here.

1090
01:26:48,260 --> 01:26:48,460
Who?

1091
01:26:49,720 --> 01:26:50,720
The Bat-Man.

1092
01:26:53,260 --> 01:26:54,100
What do we do?

1093
01:26:54,100 --> 01:26:56,980
What anyone does when a Prowler comes around.

1094
01:26:58,340 --> 01:26:59,920
Call the police.

1095
01:27:00,560 --> 01:27:01,740
You want the cops here?

1096
01:27:02,340 --> 01:27:04,260
At this point, they can't stop us.

1097
01:27:05,420 --> 01:27:08,220
But the Batman has a talent for disruption.

1098
01:27:09,060 --> 01:27:11,400
Force him outside, the police will take him down.

1099
01:27:12,080 --> 01:27:12,920
What about her?

1100
01:27:13,000 --> 01:27:14,420
She hasn't got long.

1101
01:27:14,520 --> 01:27:16,180
I give her a concentrated dose.

1102
01:27:16,940 --> 01:27:18,400
The mind can only take so much.

1103
01:27:19,040 --> 01:27:19,440
Now, go.

1104
01:27:22,000 --> 01:27:23,420
The things they say about him...

1105
01:27:24,440 --> 01:27:25,400
Can he really fly?

1106
01:27:26,200 --> 01:27:27,140
I heard he can disappear.

1107
01:27:27,340 --> 01:27:32,200
Well, we'll find out, won't we?

1108
01:28:20,840 --> 01:28:22,220
Taste of your own medicine, Doctor.

1109
01:28:27,340 --> 01:28:30,560
What have you been doing here?

1110
01:28:34,520 --> 01:28:35,520
Who are you working for?

1111
01:28:41,080 --> 01:28:41,460
Roz.

1112
01:28:42,540 --> 01:28:45,340
Roz, how cool is that?

1113
01:28:45,520 --> 01:28:47,280
Who are you working for?

1114
01:28:48,600 --> 01:28:49,440
Brain.

1115
01:28:52,080 --> 01:28:54,140
Dr. Crane isn't here right now.

1116
01:28:54,320 --> 01:28:57,720
But if you'd like to make an appointment...

1117
01:29:21,040 --> 01:29:23,100
What are you waiting for? Back up.

1118
01:29:24,320 --> 01:29:30,900
Back up. The Batman's in there. SWAT's on the way. But if you want to go in now, I'll be right behind you, sir.

1119
01:29:32,580 --> 01:29:33,560
SWAT's on the way.

1120
01:29:35,500 --> 01:29:35,680
Hey!

1121
01:30:18,880 --> 01:30:20,100
What's happened to her?

1122
01:30:20,200 --> 01:30:27,400
Crane poisoned her with a psychotropic hallucinogen, a panic-inducing toxin.

1123
01:30:29,480 --> 01:30:30,500
We get her down to the medics.

1124
01:30:31,060 --> 01:30:32,280
They can't help her, but I can.

1125
01:30:36,280 --> 01:30:39,200
Get her downstairs. Meet me in the alley on the narrow side.

1126
01:30:46,660 --> 01:30:50,040
Crane's been smuggling his toxin hidden inside Falcone's drugs.

1127
01:30:50,200 --> 01:30:51,400
in the dumping into the water supply.

1128
01:30:52,420 --> 01:30:53,900
What was he planning?

1129
01:30:54,280 --> 01:30:54,620
I don't know.

1130
01:30:54,620 --> 01:30:56,060
Was he working for Falcone?

1131
01:30:56,660 --> 01:30:57,440
He mentioned someone else.

1132
01:30:57,900 --> 01:30:58,360
Someone worse.

1133
01:30:59,160 --> 01:31:00,370
I need to get her the antidote

1134
01:31:00,370 --> 01:31:01,620
before the damage becomes permanent.

1135
01:31:02,020 --> 01:31:02,720
How long does she have?

1136
01:31:03,080 --> 01:31:03,380
Not long.

1137
01:31:07,980 --> 01:31:08,960
What is that?

1138
01:31:11,380 --> 01:31:11,800
Back up.

1139
01:31:12,480 --> 01:31:13,140
What the hell?

1140
01:31:15,660 --> 01:31:15,700
Come on!

1141
01:32:31,860 --> 01:32:32,220
Excuse me.

1142
01:32:37,480 --> 01:32:38,700
How is she?

1143
01:32:38,980 --> 01:32:40,280
She's fading. We gotta go.

1144
01:32:43,220 --> 01:32:43,860
I'll get my car.

1145
01:32:44,880 --> 01:32:45,420
I brought mine.

1146
01:32:47,060 --> 01:32:47,340
Yours.

1147
01:32:57,580 --> 01:32:59,520
I've got to get me one of those.

1148
01:33:00,720 --> 01:33:02,220
He is in a vehicle.

1149
01:33:02,600 --> 01:33:03,240
Make it color.

1150
01:33:03,560 --> 01:33:04,780
It's a black...

1151
01:33:07,200 --> 01:33:07,340
tank.

1152
01:33:10,460 --> 01:33:13,780
Stay calm. You've been poisoned.

1153
01:33:17,340 --> 01:33:18,060
I'm on him.

1154
01:33:25,660 --> 01:33:28,020
Breathe slowly.

1155
01:33:36,660 --> 01:33:39,040
Hold on.

1156
01:33:53,540 --> 01:33:54,580
What are you doing?

1157
01:33:54,840 --> 01:33:55,360
Shark guy.

1158
01:34:02,960 --> 01:34:05,180
They're on the ground. Lock that ramp.

1159
01:34:05,320 --> 01:34:11,680
I ain't got no way off that roof.

1160
01:34:13,320 --> 01:34:14,420
Turn off your engines.

1161
01:34:14,420 --> 01:34:16,160
We have to wait in the car.

1162
01:34:18,780 --> 01:34:19,380
Trust me.

1163
01:34:19,600 --> 01:34:20,820
What in the world is going on here?

1164
01:34:39,340 --> 01:34:40,100
Who is this guy?

1165
01:34:41,100 --> 01:34:41,760
Where's he going?

1166
01:34:41,760 --> 01:34:42,560
He's on the roof.

1167
01:34:56,520 --> 01:34:58,160
What street is he taking?

1168
01:34:58,420 --> 01:34:59,150
He's not on a street.

1169
01:34:59,150 --> 01:35:01,280
He's flying on rooftops.

1170
01:35:35,320 --> 01:35:42,760
At least tell me what it looks like.

1171
01:35:45,520 --> 01:35:46,240
Never mind.

1172
01:35:50,880 --> 01:35:51,400
Got him.

1173
01:36:02,480 --> 01:36:04,520
Coming right up on his butt.

1174
01:36:29,160 --> 01:36:31,320
We're tracking suspect vehicle heading west.

1175
01:36:37,520 --> 01:36:38,180
Arrow on the ground.

1176
01:36:38,180 --> 01:36:38,950
I lost him.

1177
01:36:38,950 --> 01:36:39,780
We've lost visual.

1178
01:36:40,320 --> 01:36:41,100
Exit 9's blocked.

1179
01:36:41,100 --> 01:36:43,350
We'll look back to check the frontage road.

1180
01:36:43,350 --> 01:36:44,420
Stoves activated.

1181
01:36:46,260 --> 01:36:47,080
Stay with me.

1182
01:36:53,500 --> 01:36:54,260
What? There he is!

1183
01:37:14,900 --> 01:37:15,540
Just hold on.

1184
01:37:20,420 --> 01:37:20,440
Rachel!

1185
01:37:27,560 --> 01:37:32,480
Tomorrow.

1186
01:37:35,400 --> 01:37:37,800
I'm going to go get him.

1187
01:37:54,680 --> 01:37:55,720
They get any of this crap into the mains?

1188
01:37:58,620 --> 01:37:58,660
Oh, yeah.

1189
01:37:58,660 --> 01:37:59,660
Notify the water company.

1190
01:37:59,660 --> 01:37:59,860
There's got to be a way of isolating the areas.

1191
01:38:02,600 --> 01:38:02,720
No, you don't understand.

1192
01:38:02,720 --> 01:38:03,170
They put it all in.

1193
01:38:03,170 --> 01:38:04,660
They must have been at this for weeks.

1194
01:38:05,340 --> 01:38:06,260
Why haven't we felt the effects?

1195
01:38:06,700 --> 01:38:08,380
Must be a compound that has to be absorbed to the lungs.

1196
01:38:18,640 --> 01:38:19,820
How do you feel?

1197
01:38:23,640 --> 01:38:24,320
Where are we?

1198
01:38:25,580 --> 01:38:26,520
Why did you bring me here?

1199
01:38:26,740 --> 01:38:28,740
If I hadn't, your mind would now be lost.

1200
01:38:29,600 --> 01:38:30,160
You were poisoned.

1201
01:38:30,880 --> 01:38:32,380
It was... it was Dr. Crane.

1202
01:38:32,380 --> 01:38:32,900
Dr. Crane, I...

1203
01:38:32,900 --> 01:38:34,480
Rest. Gordon has Crane.

1204
01:38:35,560 --> 01:38:36,920
Is Sergeant Gordon your friend?

1205
01:38:38,500 --> 01:38:39,940
I don't have the luxury of friends.

1206
01:38:40,940 --> 01:38:42,100
I'm gonna give you a sedative.

1207
01:38:43,220 --> 01:38:44,340
You'll wake up back at home.

1208
01:38:44,660 --> 01:38:46,580
When you do, get these to Gordon.

1209
01:38:47,000 --> 01:38:48,320
And Gordon alone trusts no one.

1210
01:38:48,800 --> 01:38:49,300
What are they?

1211
01:38:49,700 --> 01:38:50,280
The antidote.

1212
01:38:50,640 --> 01:38:53,420
One for Gordon to inoculate himself, the other for mass production.

1213
01:38:54,340 --> 01:38:55,000
Mass production?

1214
01:38:55,900 --> 01:38:56,880
Crane was just a pawn.

1215
01:38:57,940 --> 01:38:58,720
We need to be ready.

1216
01:39:25,020 --> 01:39:27,580
When you told me your grand plan for saving Gotham,

1217
01:39:28,440 --> 01:39:31,240
the only thing that stopped me from calling the men in white coats

1218
01:39:31,420 --> 01:39:33,820
was when you said that it wasn't about thrill-seeking.

1219
01:39:34,160 --> 01:39:34,580
It's not.

1220
01:39:35,340 --> 01:39:36,360
What would you call that?

1221
01:39:39,000 --> 01:39:39,880
Damn good television.

1222
01:39:39,880 --> 01:39:41,780
It's a miracle no one was killed.

1223
01:39:41,960 --> 01:39:44,720
I didn't have time to observe the rules of the road, Alfred.

1224
01:39:45,880 --> 01:39:48,020
You're getting lost inside this monster of yours.

1225
01:39:49,020 --> 01:39:53,280
I'm using this monster to help other people just like my father did.

1226
01:39:53,280 --> 01:39:57,020
But Thomas Wayne helping others wasn't about proving anything to anyone,

1227
01:39:57,480 --> 01:39:58,140
including himself.

1228
01:39:58,720 --> 01:40:00,260
It's Rachel, Alfred.

1229
01:40:01,340 --> 01:40:03,880
She was dying. She's downstairs sedated.

1230
01:40:04,180 --> 01:40:05,220
I need you to take her home.

1231
01:40:05,740 --> 01:40:07,000
Well, we both care for Rachel, sir.

1232
01:40:07,060 --> 01:40:09,200
But what you're doing has to be beyond that.

1233
01:40:09,560 --> 01:40:10,420
It can't be personal.

1234
01:40:10,880 --> 01:40:12,080
Or you're just vigilante.

1235
01:40:12,200 --> 01:40:13,300
Is Fox still here?

1236
01:40:13,820 --> 01:40:14,180
Yes, sir.

1237
01:40:14,660 --> 01:40:15,980
We need to send these people away now.

1238
01:40:16,280 --> 01:40:18,260
Those are Bruce Wayne's guests out there, sir.

1239
01:40:18,320 --> 01:40:19,620
You have a name to maintain.

1240
01:40:19,620 --> 01:40:21,300
I don't care about my name.

1241
01:40:21,600 --> 01:40:22,680
It's not just your name, sir.

1242
01:40:23,760 --> 01:40:24,720
It's your father's name.

1243
01:40:26,440 --> 01:40:27,660
And it's all that's left of him.

1244
01:40:30,400 --> 01:40:31,560
Don't destroy it.

1245
01:40:33,420 --> 01:40:35,860
Happy birthday to you.

1246
01:40:36,200 --> 01:40:38,880
Happy birthday to you.

1247
01:40:39,700 --> 01:40:42,360
Happy birthday, dear Bruce.

1248
01:40:43,440 --> 01:40:46,720
Happy birthday to you.

1249
01:40:47,640 --> 01:40:48,160
Mr. Earl.

1250
01:40:48,940 --> 01:40:49,820
Happy birthday, Bruce.

1251
01:40:49,820 --> 01:40:50,360
Thank you.

1252
01:40:51,820 --> 01:40:53,580
How'd the stock offering go?

1253
01:40:54,100 --> 01:40:54,980
Prices soared.

1254
01:40:55,480 --> 01:40:56,000
Who was buying?

1255
01:40:56,820 --> 01:40:58,500
All kinds of funds and brokerages.

1256
01:40:58,860 --> 01:40:59,620
It's a bit technical.

1257
01:41:00,400 --> 01:41:04,180
The key thing is our company's future is secure.

1258
01:41:06,240 --> 01:41:07,160
Great.

1259
01:41:19,900 --> 01:41:22,840
Little the worse for winter, I'm afraid.

1260
01:41:29,460 --> 01:41:30,600
What was the plan, Crane?

1261
01:41:31,280 --> 01:41:33,280
How were you going to get your toxin into the air?

1262
01:41:34,020 --> 01:41:34,920
Scarecrow.

1263
01:41:35,900 --> 01:41:36,860
Scarecrow.

1264
01:41:37,400 --> 01:41:38,840
Who were you working for, Crane?

1265
01:41:41,260 --> 01:41:42,100
Oh, it's too late.

1266
01:41:43,920 --> 01:41:45,060
You can't stop it now.

1267
01:41:45,220 --> 01:41:53,320
Happy birthday, Mr.

1268
01:41:53,320 --> 01:41:54,160
Well, thank you.

1269
01:41:54,740 --> 01:41:54,870
Thanks.

1270
01:41:54,870 --> 01:41:56,900
And thank you for that item.

1271
01:41:59,640 --> 01:42:00,060
You're welcome.

1272
01:42:01,100 --> 01:42:02,120
I don't know if you put it to good use.

1273
01:42:02,500 --> 01:42:03,040
I already have.

1274
01:42:03,760 --> 01:42:03,820
Hmm?

1275
01:42:04,240 --> 01:42:06,740
How long would it take to manufacture on a large scale?

1276
01:42:08,500 --> 01:42:08,810
Weeks.

1277
01:42:08,810 --> 01:42:09,340
Why?

1278
01:42:09,780 --> 01:42:12,460
Somebody's planning to disperse the toxin using the water supply.

1279
01:42:12,620 --> 01:42:16,000
Water supply won't help you disperse an inhaler.

1280
01:42:17,840 --> 01:42:18,080
What?

1281
01:42:19,540 --> 01:42:23,620
Unless you have a microwave emitter powerful enough to vaporize all the water in the mains.

1282
01:42:25,480 --> 01:42:28,540
A microwave emitter like the one Wayne Enterprises just misplaced.

1283
01:42:29,360 --> 01:42:30,080
Misplaced?

1284
01:42:30,620 --> 01:42:33,040
We're all just fired for asking too many questions about it.

1285
01:42:35,080 --> 01:42:39,000
I need you to go back to Wayne Enterprises right now and start making more of that

1286
01:42:39,080 --> 01:42:42,400
I think the police are gonna need as much as they can get their hands on, okay?

1287
01:42:43,060 --> 01:42:44,820
My security clearance has been revoked.

1288
01:42:45,440 --> 01:42:47,280
That won't stop a man like you now, would it?

1289
01:42:47,740 --> 01:42:48,380
I suppose not.

1290
01:42:51,520 --> 01:42:55,320
Bruce, there's somebody here you simply must meet.

1291
01:42:56,480 --> 01:42:58,720
Now, am I pronouncing this right?

1292
01:42:59,400 --> 01:43:01,260
Mr. Raz Al Ghul?

1293
01:43:06,740 --> 01:43:08,760
You're not Raz Al Ghul.

1294
01:43:09,080 --> 01:43:11,680
I watched him die.

1295
01:43:12,200 --> 01:43:14,000
But his horrors are all mortal.

1296
01:43:18,100 --> 01:43:19,760
Are his methods supernatural?

1297
01:43:24,980 --> 01:43:28,740
Or cheap parlor tricks to conceal your true identity, Raz.

1298
01:43:31,200 --> 01:43:35,640
Surely a man who spends his nights scrambling over the rooftops of Gotham

1299
01:43:36,100 --> 01:43:37,480
wouldn't begrudge me dual identities.

1300
01:43:38,920 --> 01:43:39,800
I saved your life.

1301
01:43:40,800 --> 01:43:42,820
I warned you about compassion, Bruce.

1302
01:43:46,460 --> 01:43:47,680
Your quarrel was with me.

1303
01:43:49,520 --> 01:43:50,740
You let these people go.

1304
01:43:52,260 --> 01:43:54,880
You are welcome to explain the situation to them.

1305
01:43:57,820 --> 01:43:58,160
Everyone?

1306
01:44:00,260 --> 01:44:00,660
Everybody?

1307
01:44:00,700 --> 01:44:10,180
I want to thank you all for coming here tonight and drinking all of my booze.

1308
01:44:13,520 --> 01:44:13,940
Not really.

1309
01:44:16,180 --> 01:44:23,980
There's a thing about being a Wayne that you're never short of a few freeloaders like yourselves to fill up your mansion with.

1310
01:44:23,980 --> 01:44:25,940
So here's to you people.

1311
01:44:26,220 --> 01:44:26,370
Thank you.

1312
01:44:26,370 --> 01:44:27,000
That's enough.

1313
01:44:28,400 --> 01:44:29,080
I'm not finished.

1314
01:44:29,340 --> 01:44:44,000
To all of you, uh, all you phonies, all you two-faced friends, you sycophantic suck-ups who smile through your teeth at me, please leave me in peace.

1315
01:44:45,240 --> 01:44:46,500
Please go.

1316
01:44:48,040 --> 01:44:53,280
Stop smiling. It's not a joke. Please leave. The party's over. Get out.

1317
01:44:54,080 --> 01:44:57,200
The apple has fallen very far from the tree, Mr. Wayne.

1318
01:45:10,780 --> 01:45:13,280
I'm using, but pointless.

1319
01:45:14,520 --> 01:45:16,180
None of these people have longed to live.

1320
01:45:16,240 --> 01:45:18,900
Your antics at the asylum have forced my hand.

1321
01:45:20,040 --> 01:45:21,580
So Crane was working for you.

1322
01:45:22,420 --> 01:45:26,040
His toxin is derived from the organic compound found in our blue flowers.

1323
01:45:26,580 --> 01:45:27,700
He was able to weaponize it.

1324
01:45:27,920 --> 01:45:30,420
He's not a member of the League of Shadows?

1325
01:45:30,600 --> 01:45:34,280
Of course not. He thought our plan was to hold the city to ransom.

1326
01:45:36,200 --> 01:45:39,880
But really you are going to release Crane's poison on the entire city.

1327
01:45:40,940 --> 01:45:44,560
Then watch Gotham tear itself apart through fear.

1328
01:45:57,840 --> 01:45:59,320
You're gonna destroy millions of lives.

1329
01:45:59,800 --> 01:46:02,880
Only a cynical man would call what these people have lives, Wayne.

1330
01:46:03,340 --> 01:46:04,280
Crime, despair.

1331
01:46:05,480 --> 01:46:07,100
This is not how man was supposed to live.

1332
01:46:08,100 --> 01:46:12,300
The League of Shadows has been a check against human corruption for thousands of years.

1333
01:46:13,020 --> 01:46:16,280
We sacked Rome, loaded trade ships with plague rats,

1334
01:46:16,940 --> 01:46:17,960
burned London to the ground.

1335
01:46:17,960 --> 01:46:21,300
Every time a civilization reaches the pinnacle of its decadence,

1336
01:46:21,720 --> 01:46:23,340
we return to restore the balance.

1337
01:46:23,520 --> 01:46:24,940
Gotham isn't beyond saving.

1338
01:46:26,400 --> 01:46:27,140
Give me more time.

1339
01:46:27,840 --> 01:46:29,180
There are good people here.

1340
01:46:29,320 --> 01:46:34,060
You are defending a city so corrupt we have infiltrated every level of its infrastructure.

1341
01:46:44,900 --> 01:46:46,260
Time to play.

1342
01:46:50,360 --> 01:46:52,800
When I found you in that jail, you were lost.

1343
01:46:54,060 --> 01:46:54,960
But I believed in you.

1344
01:46:55,100 --> 01:46:59,100
I took away your fear and I showed you a path.

1345
01:47:00,340 --> 01:47:01,500
You are my greatest student.

1346
01:47:02,900 --> 01:47:05,580
It should be you standing by my side, saving the world.

1347
01:47:06,820 --> 01:47:08,020
I'll be standing where I belong.

1348
01:47:10,000 --> 01:47:12,540
Between you and the people of Gotham.

1349
01:47:14,900 --> 01:47:16,360
No one can save Gotham.

1350
01:47:20,320 --> 01:47:24,200
When a forest grows too wild, a purging fire is inevitable and natural.

1351
01:47:25,100 --> 01:47:30,220
Tomorrow the world will watch in horror as its greatest city destroys itself.

1352
01:47:31,900 --> 01:47:34,460
The movement back to harmony will be unstoppable this time.

1353
01:47:35,460 --> 01:47:36,540
You attacked Gotham before?

1354
01:47:36,980 --> 01:47:40,200
Of course. Over the ages our weapons have grown more sophisticated.

1355
01:47:40,780 --> 01:47:42,660
With Gotham we tried a new one, economics.

1356
01:47:44,040 --> 01:47:47,400
But we underestimated certain of Gotham's citizens.

1357
01:47:49,320 --> 01:47:50,280
Such as your parents.

1358
01:47:55,100 --> 01:47:57,980
Guns down by one of the very people they were trying to help.

1359
01:47:59,200 --> 01:48:01,580
Create enough hunger and everyone becomes a criminal.

1360
01:48:02,120 --> 01:48:06,540
Their deaths galvanized the city into saving itself, and Gotham has limped on ever since.

1361
01:48:07,640 --> 01:48:09,060
We are back to finish the job.

1362
01:48:10,140 --> 01:48:12,840
This time no misguided idealists will get in the way.

1363
01:48:13,560 --> 01:48:16,520
Like your father, you lack the courage to do all that is necessary.

1364
01:48:17,480 --> 01:48:19,580
If someone stands in the way of true justice,

1365
01:48:20,460 --> 01:48:23,900
you simply walk up behind them and stab them in the heart.

1366
01:48:29,440 --> 01:48:30,430
I am gonna stop you.

1367
01:48:30,430 --> 01:48:32,520
I never did learn to mind your surroundings.

1368
01:48:36,060 --> 01:48:37,180
Justice is balance.

1369
01:48:38,360 --> 01:48:40,100
You burned my house and left me for dead.

1370
01:48:43,100 --> 01:48:44,020
Consider us even.

1371
01:49:01,740 --> 01:49:02,380
No one comes out.

1372
01:49:02,740 --> 01:49:03,120
Make sure.

1373
01:49:13,100 --> 01:49:13,780
They're all gone?

1374
01:49:14,640 --> 01:49:16,210
How many from maximum security?

1375
01:49:16,210 --> 01:49:17,500
Every one of them.

1376
01:49:18,020 --> 01:49:19,580
Serial killers, rapists.

1377
01:49:19,920 --> 01:49:20,800
Get them to raise the bridges.

1378
01:49:21,380 --> 01:49:22,620
We don't want any getting off the island.

1379
01:49:22,980 --> 01:49:23,880
I'll raise the bridges.

1380
01:49:23,980 --> 01:49:30,140
But I get every available unit out here to catch the homicidal maniacs that are running loose out there.

1381
01:49:30,480 --> 01:49:30,720
Come on.

1382
01:49:53,980 --> 01:49:57,100
I hope you're not a member of the Fibregate.

1383
01:50:03,800 --> 01:50:05,080
Fast away! Fast away!

1384
01:50:10,280 --> 01:50:13,540
What is the point of all those push-ups if you can't even lift a bloody log?

1385
01:50:52,160 --> 01:50:52,200
I'm sorry.

1386
01:50:56,460 --> 01:50:59,200
Everything my family, my father built.

1387
01:51:02,860 --> 01:51:06,020
The white legacy is more than bricks and mortar, sir.

1388
01:51:06,660 --> 01:51:10,280
I wanted to save Gotham. I failed.

1389
01:51:12,960 --> 01:51:13,960
Why do we fall, sir?

1390
01:51:17,480 --> 01:51:19,880
So that we can learn to pick ourselves up.

1391
01:51:23,300 --> 01:51:24,660
I just feel like you've given up on me.

1392
01:51:27,500 --> 01:51:27,740
Never.

1393
01:51:31,340 --> 01:51:33,060
Harassment! I see harassment!

1394
01:51:34,320 --> 01:51:36,210
Well, maybe you'd like to see some excessive force.

1395
01:51:36,210 --> 01:51:37,600
Hey, man, with your gun.

1396
01:51:40,180 --> 01:51:44,540
With residents furious at the unprecedented show of police strength to round up the inmates...

1397
01:51:44,540 --> 01:51:46,830
Well, lady, we're about to raise these bridges.

1398
01:51:46,830 --> 01:51:49,240
Officer, I'm a Gotham City District Attorney. Let me pass.

1399
01:51:57,940 --> 01:51:58,560
Hey, shut up!

1400
01:51:58,720 --> 01:51:58,960
Hold it!

1401
01:52:00,420 --> 01:52:01,300
Pull these people back!

1402
01:52:01,920 --> 01:52:03,920
Hey, Gordon, there's somebody here to see you.

1403
01:52:04,800 --> 01:52:05,580
What are you doing here?

1404
01:52:05,900 --> 01:52:07,200
A mutual friend sent me with this.

1405
01:52:07,680 --> 01:52:08,640
Counteract screen's toxic.

1406
01:52:09,300 --> 01:52:10,200
Hopefully you won't need it.

1407
01:52:11,060 --> 01:52:12,960
Unless he's got some way of getting that crap into the air.

1408
01:52:15,260 --> 01:52:16,420
All right, last one across.

1409
01:52:22,500 --> 01:52:24,160
I better get you off the island before they raise the bridges.

1410
01:52:24,160 --> 01:52:24,900
Patrolman!

1411
01:52:25,840 --> 01:52:26,060
Stop!

1412
01:52:26,400 --> 01:52:26,920
Stop!

1413
01:52:54,460 --> 01:52:55,380
I can't find my mom.

1414
01:52:55,380 --> 01:52:56,560
Hey!

1415
01:53:06,480 --> 01:53:07,260
What the hell are you doing?

1416
01:53:09,500 --> 01:53:13,100
Gentlemen, time to spread the word.

1417
01:53:15,500 --> 01:53:16,840
And the word is...

1418
01:53:18,540 --> 01:53:19,080
Panic.

1419
01:53:43,640 --> 01:53:45,700
Jesus, the pressure, it's spiking.

1420
01:53:46,820 --> 01:53:47,480
Right there.

1421
01:53:48,700 --> 01:53:50,700
That water main is right under the narrows.

1422
01:54:07,740 --> 01:54:08,180
It's okay.

1423
01:54:26,400 --> 01:54:26,960
Whoa.

1424
01:54:27,200 --> 01:54:28,220
Good devil.

1425
01:54:29,840 --> 01:54:30,760
Good devil.

1426
01:54:41,600 --> 01:54:43,300
This is Commissioner Hogue.

1427
01:54:44,080 --> 01:54:45,340
Come on, somebody talk to me.

1428
01:54:45,900 --> 01:54:46,360
Come on!

1429
01:55:07,220 --> 01:55:07,560
Oh, no!

1430
01:55:07,960 --> 01:55:08,460
This is Gordon.

1431
01:55:09,220 --> 01:55:10,540
What the hell is going on in there?

1432
01:55:10,800 --> 01:55:11,960
We need reinforcements.

1433
01:55:12,520 --> 01:55:14,220
Tact team, SWAT, riot cops.

1434
01:55:14,220 --> 01:55:14,760
Gordon!

1435
01:55:15,660 --> 01:55:18,280
All the city's riot police are on the island with you.

1436
01:55:18,280 --> 01:55:20,580
We're getting quickly incapacitated.

1437
01:55:21,260 --> 01:55:22,360
It's okay. It's okay.

1438
01:55:23,140 --> 01:55:23,880
No one's gonna hurt you.

1439
01:55:24,000 --> 01:55:27,440
Of course they are!

1440
01:55:27,900 --> 01:55:28,280
Crane?

1441
01:55:28,640 --> 01:55:30,300
No. Scarecrow.

1442
01:55:32,500 --> 01:55:35,640
Gordon, there's nobody left to send in.

1443
01:55:37,580 --> 01:55:38,480
Oh, I'm on my own?

1444
01:55:43,080 --> 01:55:45,280
The Narrows is tearing itself to pieces.

1445
01:55:45,340 --> 01:55:46,360
This is just the beginning.

1446
01:55:46,800 --> 01:55:51,080
If they hit the whole city with toxin, there's nothing to stop Gotham tearing itself apart from mass panic.

1447
01:55:51,200 --> 01:55:52,060
How are they going to do that?

1448
01:55:52,280 --> 01:55:53,100
They'll be using the train.

1449
01:55:53,220 --> 01:55:57,040
The monorail follows the water mains to the central hub beneath Wayne Tower.

1450
01:55:57,600 --> 01:56:02,480
If they get their machine into Wayne Station, it'll cause a chain reaction that'll vaporize the entire city's water supply.

1451
01:56:02,840 --> 01:56:04,640
Covering Gotham in this poison.

1452
01:56:04,700 --> 01:56:07,500
I'm gonna stop him from loading that train, but I may need your help.

1453
01:56:08,180 --> 01:56:08,600
What do you need?

1454
01:56:08,960 --> 01:56:09,660
Can you drive stick?

1455
01:56:15,820 --> 01:56:16,680
There you are.

1456
01:56:17,420 --> 01:56:18,920
There's nothing to fear.

1457
01:56:20,140 --> 01:56:21,260
But fear itself.

1458
01:56:21,640 --> 01:56:23,840
I can hear them.

1459
01:56:56,560 --> 01:56:57,680
Batman will save us.

1460
01:56:58,020 --> 01:56:58,160
Luke.

1461
01:57:03,360 --> 01:57:04,060
Luke.

1462
01:57:04,740 --> 01:57:05,190
Don't peek.

1463
01:57:05,190 --> 01:57:06,060
Ah!

1464
01:57:14,220 --> 01:57:15,040
This is Gordon.

1465
01:57:16,100 --> 01:57:17,360
Prepare to lower the bridge.

1466
01:57:21,640 --> 01:57:24,660
I told you he'd come.

1467
01:57:30,940 --> 01:57:31,040
Wait.

1468
01:57:33,220 --> 01:57:34,020
You could die.

1469
01:57:34,980 --> 01:57:35,940
At least tell me your name.

1470
01:57:41,620 --> 01:57:42,960
It's not who I am underneath.

1471
01:57:45,020 --> 01:57:45,960
But what I do...

1472
01:57:46,600 --> 01:57:47,940
That defines me.

1473
01:57:49,700 --> 01:57:50,040
Bruce?

1474
01:58:21,020 --> 01:58:21,200
I'm sorry.

1475
01:58:24,740 --> 01:58:27,800
Well, well. You took my advice about theatricality a bit. Literally.

1476
01:58:28,220 --> 01:58:29,040
It ends here.

1477
01:58:29,480 --> 01:58:32,980
For you and the police, maybe. My fate, however, lies with the rest of Gotham.

1478
01:58:33,300 --> 01:58:35,740
Now, if you'll excuse me, I have a city to destroy.

1479
01:58:36,600 --> 01:58:38,420
I can't beat two of your pawns.

1480
01:58:38,960 --> 01:58:39,460
As you wish.

1481
01:58:51,640 --> 01:58:54,440
GPS online.

1482
01:59:01,360 --> 01:59:03,420
100 yards.

1483
02:00:04,480 --> 02:00:05,480
Who the hell authorized this?

1484
02:00:16,340 --> 02:00:17,970
Extend story in town.

1485
02:00:17,970 --> 02:00:19,000
Three lines.

1486
02:00:26,620 --> 02:00:28,900
Pressure's moving along the mains, blowing all the pipes.

1487
02:00:28,900 --> 02:00:33,640
And if that pressure reaches us, the water supply right across the whole city is gonna blow!

1488
02:00:43,620 --> 02:00:46,580
At the next intersection, turn right.

1489
02:01:12,000 --> 02:01:12,980
You will never learn.

1490
02:01:26,120 --> 02:01:27,520
Amelia, don't you have anything new?

1491
02:01:27,980 --> 02:01:28,760
How about this?

1492
02:01:44,900 --> 02:01:47,800
You have arrived at Wayne Tower.

1493
02:02:01,460 --> 02:02:02,340
Evacuate the building.

1494
02:02:02,380 --> 02:02:04,840
We're right on top of the main hub, and it's gonna blow.

1495
02:02:13,460 --> 02:02:14,520
Weapons.

1496
02:02:15,440 --> 02:02:15,960
More!

1497
02:02:20,380 --> 02:02:21,100
Nice ride.

1498
02:02:49,720 --> 02:02:50,760
Don't be afraid, Bruce.

1499
02:02:51,640 --> 02:02:54,200
Come on.

1500
02:02:59,560 --> 02:03:01,940
You were just an ordinary man in a cape.

1501
02:03:02,360 --> 02:03:03,480
That's why you couldn't fight injustice,

1502
02:03:03,520 --> 02:03:05,900
and that's why you can't stop this train.

1503
02:03:06,300 --> 02:03:08,100
I'm sure there's a thing about stopping it.

1504
02:03:14,720 --> 02:03:15,100
Yes!

1505
02:03:21,640 --> 02:03:26,600
You never learned to mind your surroundings.

1506
02:03:35,460 --> 02:03:37,960
You finally learned to do what is necessary.

1507
02:03:38,560 --> 02:03:39,380
I won't kill you.

1508
02:03:44,400 --> 02:03:46,640
But I don't have to save you.

1509
02:04:21,620 --> 02:04:21,660
I'm sorry.

1510
02:05:02,720 --> 02:05:03,800
The meeting's already started.

1511
02:05:04,340 --> 02:05:05,220
What meeting?

1512
02:05:09,340 --> 02:05:10,220
Fox.

1513
02:05:10,220 --> 02:05:12,440
I seem to remember firing you.

1514
02:05:13,400 --> 02:05:13,800
You did.

1515
02:05:15,040 --> 02:05:15,940
I got another job.

1516
02:05:17,820 --> 02:05:18,220
Yours.

1517
02:05:19,940 --> 02:05:20,820
Whose authority?

1518
02:05:21,700 --> 02:05:26,440
Batman may have made the front page, but Bruce Wayne got pushed to page 8.

1519
02:05:33,800 --> 02:05:34,740
Bruce Wayne?

1520
02:05:34,740 --> 02:05:38,800
What makes you think you can decide who's running Wayne Enterprises?

1521
02:05:39,320 --> 02:05:40,420
Well, the fact that I'm the owner.

1522
02:05:40,740 --> 02:05:41,520
What are you talking about?

1523
02:05:42,260 --> 02:05:43,900
The company went public a week ago.

1524
02:05:44,380 --> 02:05:45,680
And I bought most of the shares.

1525
02:05:46,240 --> 02:05:49,140
Through various charitable foundations and trusts and so forth.

1526
02:05:49,240 --> 02:05:55,880
Look, it's all a bit technical, but the important thing is that my company's future is secure.

1527
02:05:57,060 --> 02:05:57,720
Right, Mr. Fox?

1528
02:05:58,300 --> 02:05:59,400
Right you are, Mr. Wayne.

1529
02:06:02,400 --> 02:06:03,480
Didn't you get the memo?

1530
02:06:19,240 --> 02:06:24,640
I'm sorry I didn't tell you, Rachel.

1531
02:06:24,640 --> 02:06:25,640
No, no, Bruce.

1532
02:06:26,460 --> 02:06:26,980
I'm sorry.

1533
02:06:28,320 --> 02:06:30,500
The day that Chill died, I...

1534
02:06:33,160 --> 02:06:34,400
I said terrible things.

1535
02:06:35,400 --> 02:06:36,020
But true things.

1536
02:06:37,640 --> 02:06:39,200
I was a coward with a gun.

1537
02:06:39,840 --> 02:06:43,260
Justice is about more than revenge, so thank you.

1538
02:06:44,460 --> 02:06:46,300
I never stopped thinking about you.

1539
02:06:48,920 --> 02:06:49,380
about us.

1540
02:06:51,180 --> 02:06:52,200
And when I heard you were back,

1541
02:06:52,340 --> 02:06:54,880
I started to hope.

1542
02:07:16,460 --> 02:07:21,760
Then I found out about your mask.

1543
02:07:24,000 --> 02:07:25,520
My mask's just a symbol, Rachel.

1544
02:07:27,360 --> 02:07:30,720
No, this is your mask.

1545
02:07:33,480 --> 02:07:36,640
Your real face is the one that criminals now fear.

1546
02:07:36,640 --> 02:07:39,120
The man I loved.

1547
02:07:41,000 --> 02:07:41,800
The man who vanished.

1548
02:07:43,820 --> 02:07:44,940
He never came back at all.

1549
02:07:46,460 --> 02:07:52,000
But maybe he's still out there somewhere.

1550
02:07:55,100 --> 02:08:00,600
Maybe someday when Gotham no longer needs Batman, we'll see him again.

1551
02:08:13,020 --> 02:08:13,980
Who's me wrong, you know?

1552
02:08:14,520 --> 02:08:14,880
About what?

1553
02:08:18,500 --> 02:08:20,120
My father would be very proud of you.

1554
02:08:21,380 --> 02:08:22,000
Just like me.

1555
02:08:50,100 --> 02:08:50,640
What will you do?

1556
02:08:53,280 --> 02:08:53,780
Rebuild it.

1557
02:08:55,520 --> 02:08:57,180
Just the way it was, brick for brick.

1558
02:09:01,460 --> 02:09:05,940
Just the way it was, sir?

1559
02:09:08,360 --> 02:09:08,780
Yeah, why?

1560
02:09:09,560 --> 02:09:13,740
I thought this might be a good opportunity for improving the foundations.

1561
02:09:15,320 --> 02:09:16,360
In the southeast corner.

1562
02:09:17,500 --> 02:09:18,140
Precisely, sir.

1563
02:09:34,100 --> 02:09:34,120
Nice.

1564
02:09:35,200 --> 02:09:36,620
I couldn't find any mob bosses.

1565
02:09:37,680 --> 02:09:38,420
Well, Sergeant.

1566
02:09:38,940 --> 02:09:40,160
Oh, it's Lieutenant now.

1567
02:09:40,680 --> 02:09:41,820
He really started something.

1568
02:09:42,480 --> 02:09:44,040
Mad cops running scared.

1569
02:09:44,080 --> 02:09:45,660
Hope on the streets.

1570
02:09:46,360 --> 02:09:46,560
But?

1571
02:09:47,320 --> 02:09:48,740
The Narrows is lost.

1572
02:09:50,500 --> 02:09:53,840
I still haven't picked up Crane or half the inmates of Arkham that he freed.

1573
02:09:54,900 --> 02:09:55,440
We will.

1574
02:09:56,620 --> 02:09:58,080
We can bring Gotham back.

1575
02:09:58,080 --> 02:09:59,560
What about Escalation?

1576
02:10:00,020 --> 02:10:00,640
Escalation?

1577
02:10:00,760 --> 02:10:04,720
We start carrying semi-automatics, they buy automatics.

1578
02:10:05,640 --> 02:10:09,680
We start wearing Kevlar, they buy armor-piercing rounds.

1579
02:10:10,460 --> 02:10:15,560
And you're wearing a mask, jumping off rooftops.

1580
02:10:16,900 --> 02:10:18,000
Now take this guy.

1581
02:10:19,620 --> 02:10:21,000
Armed robbery, double homicide.

1582
02:10:21,780 --> 02:10:24,780
Had a taste for the theatrical, like you.

1583
02:10:25,360 --> 02:10:26,280
Leaves a calling card.

1584
02:10:30,760 --> 02:10:33,840
I'll look into it.

1585
02:10:37,460 --> 02:10:39,540
I never said thank you.

1586
02:10:44,460 --> 02:10:45,940
And you'll never have to.

